# Frontend (React 19 / TypeScript / Vite / Tailwind v4 / shadcn/ui)

## TypeScript
- Strict mode; no `any` — use `unknown` + type guards instead
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Use Zod schemas as single source of truth; infer types with `z.infer<>`

## React
- Functional components only; no `React.FC` — use plain typed props
- Colocate hooks, types, and utils next to their component
- Use TanStack Query for all server state; no `useEffect` for data fetching
- Use TanStack Router for routing; define route params with Zod validation
- Error boundaries around every route; use `react-error-boundary`

## shadcn/ui + Tailwind
- Use existing shadcn components from `components/ui/`; add new ones via CLI
- Compose with `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) — never raw string concat
- Tailwind v4: use CSS-first config; prefer utility classes over custom CSS
- Keep component variants in CVA (`class-variance-authority`)
- Use `lucide-react` for icons; keep icon imports tree-shakeable

## Forms
- React Hook Form + Zod resolver for all forms
- Define schemas in a shared file; reuse between frontend validation and API types

## Linting
- Biome is configured; run `bun run lint` before committing
